<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-1417] investigate differences in client last zxid handling btw c and java clients</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-1417</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-1412&quot; title=&quot;java client watches inconsistently triggered on reconnect&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-1412&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ZOOKEEPER-1412&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; it was identified that the c and java clients handle updating the last zxid seen a bit differently. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-1412&quot; title=&quot;java client watches inconsistently triggered on reconnect&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-1412&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ZOOKEEPER-1412&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed a bug associated with this, however there are still some differences that should be investigated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
