                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13673729" author="thawan" created="Mon, 3 Jun 2013 23:50:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Modify c-client to match Java behavior. Only update lastZxid when receiving request response (ignore zxid from ping and watch notification)  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13673740" author="thawan" created="Mon, 3 Jun 2013 23:58:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is my current understanding on how this part works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The client receives 3 types of responses: ping, watch notification and request response. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ping: we should ignore its zxid&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Watch notification: when watch is triggered, it will be remove from the list of active watchers, so last zxid delivered as part of notification shouldn&apos;t affect how watches are being triggered on reconnect&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;request response: we should always update last zxid when receive this type of packet.   &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
